
[1]torrent

   TOR'RENT, n. [L. torrens. This is the participle of torreo, to parch;
   Eng. tear.]

   1. A violent rushing stream of water or other fluid; a stream suddenly
   raised and running rapidly, as down a precipice; as a torrent of lava.

   2. A violent or rapid stream; a strong current; as a torrent of vices
   and follies; a torrent of corruption.

   Erasmus, that great injur'd name,

   Stemm'd the wild torrent of a barb'rous age.

   TOR'RENT, a. Rolling or rushing in a rapid stream; as waves of torrent
                                    fire.
